Since G and H are binomial random graphs, they are AEMeasurable. This means that for any set A, the sets {ω | G ω ∈ A} and {ω | H ω ∈ A} are measurable. 

Now, the set {ω | G ω ⊓ H ω ∈ A} is the intersection of {ω | G ω ∈ A} and {ω | H ω ∈ A}. Because the intersection of two measurable sets is measurable, {ω | G ω ⊓ H ω ∈ A} is measurable. 

Therefore, f is AEMeasurable.

